ce:section.ce:para:
Triplex distilled water was used in the whole experimental process and to prepare PBS buffers. Graphite power, sodium borohydride, tetrahydrofuran, 1-ethyl-3-(3-dimethyllaminopropyl) carbodiimide hydrochloride (EDC·HCl), N-hydroxysuccinimide (NHS) were purchased from Aladdin Ltd. (Shanghai, China). All spectra detections were carried out at pH 7.4 phosphate buffer solution (PBS), which was prepared by mixing stock solutions of NaH2PO4 and Na2HPO4. All reagents were of analytical grade and without any further purification. DNA oligonucleotides with a concentration of 100.0μM were purchased from Sangon (Shanghai, China) and purified using high-performance liquid chromatography, their sequences are listed as follows:
Capture ssDNA sequence:
5′-NH2-TTGGTGAAGCTAACGTTGAGG-3′;
Target ssDNA sequence (perfect match with capture ssDNA):
5′-CCTCAACGTTAGCTTCACCAA-3′;
Single-base mismatched ssDNA sequence (mDNA-1):
5′-CCTCAACGTT C GCTTCACCAA-3′;
Two-base mismatched ssDNA sequence (mDNA-2):
5′-CCTCA T CGTT C GCTTCACCAA-3′;
Three-base mismatched ssDNA sequence (mDNA-3):
5′-CCTCA T CGTT C GCTTC T CCAA-3′.
